  "texts": [
    "The response ⟨ϕ 0 ⟩ H+δH at the (n -1) th power in δH is then determined by the n-point correlators of field differences, namelyR 0 {ϕ 0 ϕ 1 • • • ϕ n-1 } ≡ C{ϕ I 0 ϕ (I-II) 1 • • • ϕ (I-II) n-1 } = I II Re t Im t φ (I-II) 1 φ (I-II) n-1 φ I 0 • • •, (4.25)-24 - JHEP01(2024)139where ϕ(I-II) k (x) ≡ ϕ I k (x) -ϕ II k (x)is inserted on the two folds.",
    "The same perturbation is inserted on the two branches with a relative minus sign because the same δH is used to evolve both the bra and the ket.",
    "Expanding the C products, one finds, e.g., for n = 2, 3:R 2 {ϕ 1 ϕ 2 } = [ϕ 2, ϕ 1]θ(x 0 2 -x 0 1), (4.26a) R 3 {ϕ 1 ϕ 2 ϕ 3 } = [[ϕ 3, ϕ 2], ϕ 1]θ(x 0 3 -x 0 2)θ(x 0 2 -x 0 1) + (1↔2).",
    "(4.26b)The explicit formula for the n-point retarded product defined in (4.25) involves a similar nested commutator summed over (n-1)!",
    "permutations of the sources."
  ],
